 1.e4 c5 2.Nf3 d6 3.d4 cxd4 4.Nxd4 Nf6 5.Nc3 a6 6.Be2 e5 7.Nb3 Be7 8.O-O O-O 9.f4 exf4 ( 9...b5 $1 ) 10.Bxf4 Be6 11.Nd4 Nbd7 12.Kh1 Ne5 { But cannot White destroy our pawn structure now? } 13.Bxe5 $2 dxe5 14.Nxe6 fxe6 15.Qxd8 ( { Or } 15.Bc4 Qc8 16.Bb3 b5 $15 ) 15...Rfxd8 16.Bc4 Kf7 $1 { None of Black's pawns are weak. Quite the contrary they control all important central squares, making White's knight a sorry sight for the rest of the game. The only weak pawn on the board is the one on e4, which will be in distress soon, for example } 17.Bd3 ( 17.g4 $2 g5 18.h4 h6 19.hxg5 hxg5 20.Kg2 Bb4 21.Ne2 Ke7 $17 ) ( 17.Rad1 Bb4 $15 ) 17...Bc5 18.Rad1 Ke7 $17 19.Ne2 $2 ( 19.h3 b5 $15 ) 19...Ng4 $19 

