 1.e4 c5 2.Nf3 d6 3.d4 cxd4 4.Nxd4 Nf6 5.Nc3 a6 6.Be3 e5 7.Nb3 Be6 8.Be2 Be7 9.O-O O-O 10.Bf3 Nbd7 11.a4 Rc8 12.Nd5 Bxd5 ( 12...Nxd5 $5 13.exd5 Bf5 14.c3 Bg6 $1 { Followed by f7-f5. } ) 13.exd5 Ne8 $1 14.Rc1 f5 ( 14...Bg5 $5 ) 15.c4 a5 $1 { Fixing White's pawns and taking control of the dark squares. Note that this move is only good because White has a pawn on c4. Otherwise, it would give White's bishop access to the b5-square, which should be avoided at all cost. } ( { Less precise is } 15...b6 $6 16.a5 $1 bxa5 17.Ra1 $36 ) 16.Be2 b6 17.f3 ( 17.f4 Nc5 18.Nxc5 bxc5 19.fxe5 dxe5 $17 ) 17...Nc5 $17 ( 17...Bg5 $17 ) 18.Nxc5 bxc5 19.Qd2 Rb8 20.Rc3 Nf6 21.Bd3 g6 22.Bh6 Rf7 $17 { Black's strong central majority will sooner or later move forward. The same can hardly be said about White's b-pawn. } 

