 1.e4 c5 2.Nf3 d6 3.d4 cxd4 4.Nxd4 Nf6 5.Nc3 a6 6.Be3 e5 7.Nf3 { This prevents Black from playing ...Be6, which can now be met with Ng5. } 7...Qc7 { In return, Black prevents White from playing Bc4. } 8.Be2 Be7 9.a4 O-O ( 9...h6 10.a5 Be6 11.Nd5 Nxd5 ( 11...Bxd5 12.exd5 Nbd7 13.c4 $14 O-O-O ) 12.exd5 Bg4 ( 12...Bf5 $6 13.c4 O-O 14.b4 $14 ) ) 10.O-O b6 $2 { The queenside fianchetto would be justified if White had played f2-f4 already. Now e4 is not a weakness, though, as it can be fortified with f2-f3 anytime. } 11.Qd3 Nbd7 12.Qc4 Qxc4 13.Bxc4 Bb7 14.Nd2 Rac8 15.Rfd1 Rc7 16.f3 Rfc8 17.b3 h5 18.Bf2 Kf8 19.Nf1 g6 20.Ne3 $16 Ke8 21.Kf1 Bf8 22.Rd2 Be7 23.Rad1 Ra8 24.Ncd5 Nxd5 25.Bxd5 b5 26.Ra1 Rac8 27.axb5 axb5 28.Bxb7 Rxb7 29.Nd5 Bf8 30.c3 f5 31.Rda2 Kf7 32.Ra7 Rcb8 33.Rxb7 Rxb7 34.Ra8 Be7 35.Ke2 Nf6 36.Nxf6 Kxf6 37.Kd3 Ke6 38.Rg8 Kf7 39.Rc8 Ke6 40.Be3 Rd7 41.Rg8 Bf6 42.Rxg6 f4 43.Bf2 Kf7 44.Rh6 Kg7 45.Rxh5 Kg6 46.Rf5 Rh7 47.h4 Kf7 48.g4 fxg3 49.Bxg3 Ke6 50.h5 d5 51.Be1 Rd7 52.h6 dxe4+ 53.Kxe4 b4 54.Bg3 Bh8 55.Rf8 Bf6 56.Bxe5 Bxe5 57.Re8+ Re7 58.Rxe7+ Kxe7 59.cxb4 Bc3 60.b5 Kd6 61.f4 

