 { HOW SHOULD BLACK CONTINUE HERE?? } 1...Bxd5 $3 $15 { From a strategical standpoint this exchange is usually not desirable, but here we use the concrete factors of the position: the hanging e4-pawn and g4-bishop. } 2.Qxd5 ( 2.exd5 f5 3.Be2 Rc8 $15 { is typically very good for Black. } ) 2...Nf6 3.Qd1 Nxe4 $17 4.Bf3 d5 5.c4 { What to play now? } 5...Rc8 $3 { We allow White to regain the pawn on d5 in order to establish a perfect blockade with ...Nd6. } ( 5...dxc4 6.Bxe4 cxb3 7.Qxb3 Rb8 8.Rad1 Qe7 $15 { is only slightly better as we have the opposite-colored bishops and the white bishop is significantly more effective. } ) 6.cxd5 ( 6.Qxd5 Qxd5 7.cxd5 Nd6 $17 { is similar, with an additional ...Rc2 threat. } ) 6...Nd6 $17 7.Re1 Re8 { The strategic initiative is firmly in Black's hands. } 

