 1.e4 c5 2.Nf3 d6 3.d4 cxd4 4.Nxd4 Nf6 5.Nc3 a6 6.Be2 e5 7.Nb3 Be7 8.O-O O-O 9.Be3 Be6 10.Qd2 Nbd7 11.a4 Rc8 12.Rfd1 Qc7 $6 { It is surprising the Carlsen forgot 12...Nb6! =+ } ( 12...Nb6 $1 13.a5 Nc4 14.Bxc4 Rxc4 15.f3 Qc8 $15 ) 13.a5 Rfd8 14.Qe1 h6 15.Nc1 Qb8 16.N1a2 Ng4 17.Bxg4 ( { In the case of } 17.Bd2 { Black could weaken White's kingside: } 17...Bh4 18.g3 Be7 $132 ) 17...Bxg4 18.Rd2 ( 18.Nd5 $1 $36 { was much more energetic and strong. } ) 18...Nf6 19.f3 Be6 $132 20.Qd1 ( 20.Nb4 { is not successful: } 20...Rc4 21.Nbd5 Nxd5 22.Nxd5 Bxd5 23.exd5 Qc8 24.c3 Qd7 $17 { There are too many weaknesses in White's camp here. } ( { or } 24...Bg5 25.Bxg5 hxg5 26.h3 Qc5+ $17 ) ) 20...Rc4 21.b3 Rcc8 22.Rd3 Rd7 23.Qd2 $4 { A tactical mistake that cost White the game. } 23...d5 $1 $19 { Carlsen doesn't miss his chance to strike. Just like that, White is lost. } 24.Bf2 ( 24.exd5 Bf5 $19 ) ( 24.Nxd5 Bxd5 25.exd5 e4 { Black's initiative here should be sufficient to win, e.g. } 26.fxe4 Nxe4 27.Qe2 Bd6 28.g3 Re7 $19 ) 24...dxe4 25.Rxd7 Bxd7 26.Nxe4 Nxe4 27.fxe4 Bc6 28.Qe2 Qd6 29.Rd1 Qa3 30.Nc3 Qxa5 31.Nd5 Bxd5 32.exd5 Bd6 33.c4 Re8 34.Qe3 Rc8 35.Rc1 Bc5 36.Qe2 e4 37.Rd1 e3 38.Bg3 Qc3 39.d6 Qxb3 40.Rd5 Qb1+ 41.Qe1 Qxe1+ 42.Bxe1 b6 43.Kf1 Rd8 44.Bg3 Rd7 45.Ke2 f6 46.Bf4 Kf7 

