 1.e4 c5 2.Nf3 d6 3.d4 cxd4 4.Nxd4 Nf6 5.Nc3 a6 6.h3 e5 7.Nde2 h5 8.g3 Be7 9.Bg2 b5 10.a3 $6 { White should play 10.a4 or 10.Nd5. Passive play with a3 is a welcome sign for Black. } 10...Bb7 11.O-O Nbd7 12.f4 $6 { This only helps Black's cause, as the e4 pawn becomes a glaring weakness. } 12...O-O 13.f5 Rc8 14.Kh2 Nc5 15.Be3 Ncxe4 $19 { Black won the central pawn without any compensation whatsoever. This is a blitz game and the latter part is not very relevant. } 16.Nxe4 Bxe4 17.c3 Bxg2 18.Kxg2 Qd7 19.Ng1 Qc6+ 20.Kh2 Qe4 21.Qd2 h4 22.g4 d5 23.Bf2 Nh7 24.Rae1 Qc4 25.Nf3 Bd6 26.Nxh4 d4 27.cxd4 exd4+ 28.Kh1 d3 29.Ng2 Rfd8 30.Rd1 Be5 31.Rfe1 Bb8 32.Be3 Qd5 33.Bf4 Ba7 34.Qb4 Rc2 35.Rd2 Bc5 36.Qa5 Bf8 37.Red1 Rxd2 38.Rxd2 Nf6 39.Kh2 Ne4 40.Rd1 Rd7 41.Ne3 Qb3 42.Qe1 Qxb2+ 43.Ng2 Re7 44.Qf1 d2 45.Qd3 Nf2 46.Qxd2 Nxd1 47.Qxd1 Re2 48.Qd5 Qa2 49.Qa8 Qxa3 50.Bg3 Qe7 51.Qxa6 Qe4 52.Qc8 Qxg2# 

