 { This game is one of the most famous positional masterpieces of all time. } 1.e4 c5 2.Nf3 d6 3.d4 cxd4 4.Nxd4 Nf6 5.Nc3 a6 6.g3 e5 7.Nde2 Be7 8.Bg5 Nbd7 9.Bh3 ( { In my view, White should play } 9.a4 { to prevent ...b5. } 9...b6 $13 { Compared to the Najdorf with the knight on b3, this type of setup is fully acceptable for Black. } ) 9...b5 10.a4 b4 11.Nd5 Nxd5 12.Qxd5 Rb8 13.Bxe7 Kxe7 $1 { The king is actually very safe in the centre. Black is threatening ... Nf6. White's knight has no access to the d5-square. } 14.Qd2 Nf6 15.Bg2 ( 15.Bxc8 Qxc8 16.f3 Qc5 $17 { Black has a very nice advantage because of White's problems with the passive e2-knight that needs a lot of time to get activated. } ) 15...Bb7 16.Qd3 Qb6 ( { Compared to other nationalities, Russian players have a tendency to fix the structure as soon as possible to clarify the game and build on their static advantages later. No doubt many of them would play } 16...a5 $1 $17 { immediately, which happens to be the best move. } ) 17.O-O $6 ( { White could disrupt Black's plans a bit and limit his advantage with } 17.a5 $1 ) 17...a5 $1 { Black starts getting control over the whole board now. } 18.Rfd1 Ba6 19.Qd2 Rhc8 20.h3 h5 $3 { Black stops the g3-g4-Ng3 idea to completely limit the knight on e2 before proceeding with action on the queenside. } 21.b3 ( 21.Rac1 Rc7 $17 { The plan is to increase pressure on the queenside. } ) 21...Bxe2 { The plan has changed now that the c3-square can be accessed by Black's rook. } 22.Qxe2 Rc3 23.Rd3 Rbc8 24.Rxc3 Rxc3 25.Kh2 Qc5 26.Ra2 { This is painfully passive, but White tries to hold on to the material. } ( { After } 26.Rc1 { Black had a winning tactical shot: } 26...Rxb3 27.cxb3 Qxc1 28.Qa6 Qc7 29.Kg1 g6 30.Qa8 { White tries some activity. The accurate way to win now is } 30...Qc3 $1 31.Qxa5 Qxb3 $19 { Black's pawn is faster. } ) 26...g6 27.Bf1 Qd4 $19 { Black achieves total domination and White is not able to hold on for long. } 28.f3 Re3 29.Qg2 Qd1 30.Bc4 Qxf3 31.Qxf3 Rxf3 32.Kg2 Re3 33.Bd3 Nxe4 34.Bxe4 Rxe4 35.Kf2 d5 36.Ra1 d4 37.Rd1 Re3 38.h4 Rc3 39.Rd2 Ke6 40.Kg2 f5 

