 { A very instructive game with all its mistakes! } 1.e4 { [%emt 0:00:02] } 1...c5 { [%emt 0:00:02] } 2.Nf3 { [%emt 0:00:02] } 2...d6 { [%emt 0:00:01] } 3.d4 { [%emt 0:00: 00] } 3...cxd4 { [%emt 0:00:00] } 4.Nxd4 { [%emt 0:00:00] } 4...Nf6 { [%emt 0:00:00] } 5.Nc3 { [%emt 0:00:01] } 5...a6 { [%emt 0:00:00] } 6.g3 { [%emt 0:00:01] } 6...e5 { [%emt 0:00:03] } 7.Nde2 { [%emt 0:00:02] } 7...Be7 { [%emt 0:00:06] } 8.Bg2 { [%emt 0:00:00] } 8...O-O { [%emt 0:00:01] } 9.h3 { [%emt 0:00:02] } 9...b5 { [%emt 0:00:02] } 10.Be3 $6 { [%emt 0: 00:03] } ( 10.Nd5 $1 { REMEMBER THE GOLDEN RULE: IN THE g3 NAJDORF BLACK SHOULD NOT BE ALLOWED TO PLAY BOTH ...b5 AND ...Nbd7 WITHOUT ACTIVE PLAY BY WHITE!... SO AFTER 1...Nbd7 2. a4! is the move and after 1...b5 2.Nd5! or 2.a4! is the move!! } ) 10...Bb7 $6 { [%emt 0:00:03] } ( 10...Nbd7 $1 { This is the most accurate... with great counterplay for Black! It is not yet sure where we will develop the light-squared bishop, e.g. } 11.g4 b4 12.Nd5 Nxd5 13.exd5 a5 14.Ng3 Ba6 { and Black benefits from not having developed the bishop to b7 too early. } ) 11.O-O { [%emt 0:00:06] } 11...Nbd7 { [%emt 0:00:02] } 12.g4 { [%emt 0:00:11] } 12...b4 $1 { [%emt 0:00:07] } ( { We don't want to play quiet moves and allow Ng3 with the Nf5 threat, e.g. } 12...Rc8 $6 13.Ng3 g6 14.Bh6 $1 { the point being } 14...Re8 $2 15.g5 $1 { with huge trouble. } ) 13.Nd5 { [%emt 0:00:02] } 13...Nxd5 { [%emt 0:00: 01] } 14.exd5 { [%emt 0:00:00] } 14...Bg5 { [%emt 0:00:08] Black utilizes the typical idea of exchanging the dark-squared bishops. } 15.Qd2 { [%emt 0:00:14] } 15...Bxe3 { [%emt 0:00:02] } 16.Qxe3 { [%emt 0:00:00] Black is better here. There was a lot of mistakes in the remaining part of the game because it's a blitz game. } 16...a5 { [%emt 0:00:05] } ( { Black had a very strong idea of seriously weakening White's kingside with } 16...h5 $1 $17 ) 17.Ng3 { [%emt 0:00:05] } 17...Rc8 { [%emt 0:00:03] } 18.Rac1 { [%emt 0:00:05] } 18...Qb6 { [%emt 0:00:05] } 19.Qd2 { [%emt 0:00:06] } 19...Rfe8 { [%emt 0:00:06] } 20.Rfe1 { [%emt 0:00:07] } 20...Rc4 { [%emt 0:00:07] } 21.c3 { [%emt 0: 00:23] } 21...bxc3 { [%emt 0:00:06] } 22.Rxc3 { [%emt 0:00:03] } 22...Rd4 { [%emt 0:00:00] } 23.Rd3 { [%emt 0:00:01] } 23...Rxd3 { [%emt 0:00:03] } 24.Qxd3 { [%emt 0:00:00] } 24...Qxb2 { [%emt 0:00:21] } 25.Rb1 { [%emt 0:00:10] } 25...Ba6 { [%emt 0:00:01] } 26.Qf5 { [%emt 0: 00:01] } 26...Qxa2 { [%emt 0:00:02] } 27.Rc1 { [%emt 0:00:43] } 27...Nc5 { [%emt 0:00:12] } 28.h4 { [%emt 0:00:06] } 28...Bd3 { [%emt 0:00:04] } 29.Qg5 { [%emt 0:00:00] } 29...h6 { [%emt 0: 00:03] } 30.Qe3 { [%emt 0:00:01] } 30...Bh7 { [%emt 0:00:14] } 31.g5 { [%emt 0:00:01] } 31...hxg5 { [%emt 0:00:00] } 32.Qxg5 { [%emt 0:00:01] } 32...f6 { [%emt 0:00:11] } 33.Qg4 { [%emt 0:00:02] } 33...Qd2 { [%emt 0:00:02] } 34.Ra1 { [%emt 0:00:03] } 34...f5 { [%emt 0:00: 06] } 35.Qh3 { [%emt 0:00:09] } 35...Rf8 { [%emt 0:00:05] } 36.Nf1 { [%emt 0:00:01] } 36...Qb4 { [%emt 0:00:05] } 37.h5 { [%emt 0:00:03] } 37...a4 { [%emt 0:00:04] } 38.h6 { [%emt 0: 00:01] } 38...Qg4 { [%emt 0:00:01] } 39.hxg7 { [%emt 0:00:06] } 39...Kxg7 { [%emt 0:00:03] } 40.Qc3 { [%emt 0:00:06] } 40...f4 { [%emt 0:00:03] } 41.Nh2 { [%emt 0:00:01] } 41...Qh5 { [%emt 0:00:01] } 42.Qa5 { [%emt 0:00:06] } 42...Rf7 { [%emt 0:00:06] } 43.Qb6 { [%emt 0: 00:01] } 43...Qg6 { [%emt 0:00:04] } 44.Kh1 { [%emt 0:00:02] } 44...Qh6 { [%emt 0:00:05] } 45.Bf3 { [%emt 0:00:04] } 45...Kh8 { [%emt 0:00:01] } 46.Qd8+ { [%emt 0:00:07] } 46...Qf8 { [%emt 0:00:01] } 47.Qh4 { [%emt 0:00:02] } 47...Qe7 { [%emt 0:00:01] } 48.Bh5 { [%emt 0: 00:01] } 48...Qxh4 { [%emt 0:00:01] } 

