 1.e4 c5 2.Nf3 d6 3.d4 cxd4 4.Nxd4 Nf6 5.Nc3 a6 6.g3 e5 7.Nb3 Be7 8.Bg2 O-O 9.O-O Be6 10.Re1 Nbd7 11.a4 Qb8 $1 ( 11...Qc7 $1 { is the other good move and the main recommendation. } 12.Nd5 { is not to be feared at all: } 12...Nxd5 13.exd5 Bf5 14.c3 Bg6 $11 ) 12.Nd2 { White continues with the only sensible plan, i.e. Nd2-f1-e3. } 12...Bd8 13.a5 ( 13.Nf1 Bb6 14.Ne3 Qc7 $132 { Having transferred the bishop to an excellent diagonal, we are doing very well. } ) 13...b5 14.axb6 Bxb6 15.h3 ( { In case of a random move like } 15.Ra3 $2 { there is a phenomenal tactical shot lurking: } 15...Bxf2+ $1 ( { Incidentally, in this case } 15...Bc5 $3 { and ...Bxf2+! next is even more killing. } ) 16.Kxf2 Qa7+ 17.Kf1 Ng4 18.Re2 Nxh2+ 19.Ke1 Qg1+ 20.Bf1 ( 20.Nf1 Bh3 $3 $19 { is the whole point. } ) 20...Qxg3+ 21.Rf2 Ng4 $17 { with a very big advantage. } ) ( 15.Nf1 { allows an unpleasant attack against f2: } 15...Ng4 { with a sample line: } 16.Be3 Nxe3 17.Nxe3 Bxe3 18.Rxe3 Qxb2 19.Rb1 Qa3 20.Nb5 $6 ( 20.Nd5 $11 { should be equal instead. } ) 20...Qxe3 $1 21.fxe3 axb5 $15 { Black has more than sufficient compensation for the queen. } ) 15...Bd4 ( 15...a5 $5 { playing for the typical idea of ...a5-a4-a3 in such positions! } ) 16.Na4 h6 17.Nf1 Rc8 18.Be3 Bxe3 $6 { Black faced some problems after this trade. } ( { A move like } 18...Bc5 $11 { was recommended, not giving White the knight improvement with a tempo and having a perfectly good game. } ) 19.Nxe3 $14 { White became slightly better and later held some winning chances, although the game was eventually drawn. If you are interested, you can investigate the rest of the game for yourself. We have already shown the key opening ideas. } 19...a5 20.Nf5 Bxf5 21.exf5 Ra7 22.Re3 Rc4 23.Rd3 Ra6 24.b3 Rb4 25.Nc3 e4 26.Rd4 Nc5 27.Qd2 Qe8 28.Rxb4 axb4 29.Rxa6 bxc3 30.Qxd6 Nxa6 31.Qxa6 Qd8 32.Qe2 Qd2 33.Bf1 e3 34.fxe3 Nd5 35.e4 Ne3 36.Kf2 Kf8 37.e5 Ke7 38.g4 g6 39.Qxd2 cxd2 40.Be2 d1=Q 41.Bxd1 Nxd1+ 42.Ke2 Nc3+ 43.Kd3 Nd1 44.b4 Nf2+ 45.Ke3 Nxh3 46.b5 gxf5 47.gxf5 Ng5 48.Kf4 Nh7 49.b6 Nf8 50.b7 Nd7 51.c4 Kd8 52.e6 fxe6 53.fxe6 Nb8 54.Ke5 Kc7 55.e7 Nc6+ 56.Ke6 Nxe7 57.Kxe7 Kxb7 58.Kd7 Kb6 59.Kd6 Kb7 

