 { a very instructive game ...regardless of the variation (a ...delayed h4 Najdorf !) } 1.e4 c5 2.Nf3 d6 3.d4 cxd4 4.Nxd4 Nf6 5.Nc3 a6 6.Be3 e5 7.Nb3 Be6 8.Be2 Be7 9.h4 { first time I saw this move in my life! } 9...h5 { and I decided to play more solid chess ! } ( 9...Nbd7 10.g4 h6 ) ( 9...O-O $1 10.g4 d5 ) 10.Nd5 Bxd5 ( 10...Nbd7 11.f3 ( 11.Nxe7 Qxe7 12.Bg5 O-O-O 13.c4 ) 11...Bxd5 12.exd5 Rc8 13.Qd2 ( 13.c4 ) 13...Nb6 ) 11.exd5 Nbd7 12.c4 Rc8 13.a4 $6 a5 14.Nd2 g6 15.g3 Nc5 { in the end i didnt like this move although its the computer's first choice } 16.O-O O-O 17.Kg2 Qd7 ( 17...Nfd7 $1 18.Nf3 ( 18.g4 hxg4 19.Bxg4 f5 $17 ) 18...f5 19.Ng5 Bxg5 20.Bxg5 Qe8 $36 ) 18.f3 ( 18.f4 $5 $36 { this is what i told him that he should have played } ) 18...e4 $1 19.f4 $2 Qf5 20.Re1 Rfe8 21.Bd4 Bd8 $1 ( 21...Bf8 22.Nf1 Ng4 ( 22...Nd3 $4 23.Ne3 $3 Nxe1+ 24.Qxe1 Qd7 25.Bxf6 ) 23.Bxg4 Qxg4 24.Qxg4 hxg4 25.Bxc5 Rxc5 26.Ne3 ) ( 21...Nd3 $2 22.Bxd3 exd3 23.Qf3 Bf8 24.b3 Bg7 25.Rad1 $16 ) 22.Nf1 Nd3 23.Bxd3 exd3 24.Nd2 $2 ( 24.Rxe8+ Nxe8 25.Qf3 Bf6 26.Ne3 Qd7 27.Bxf6 Nxf6 28.b3 ( 28.f5 Qe7 $15 ) 28...Re8 29.Rd1 Ne4 30.Rxd3 Nc5 31.Rc3 f5 $36 { this i calculated well in advance } ) 24...Rxe1 25.Qxe1 Rxc4 ( 25...Kf8 $3 26.Ra3 ( 26.Qf2 Ne4 ) 26...Bb6 $3 $17 { houdini ... } 27.Bxb6 Re8 28.Be3 Ng4 29.Nf1 Rxe3 ) 26.Bxf6 Bxf6 27.Nxc4 Qxd5+ 28.Kh2 Qxc4 29.Qd2 Bd4 30.Ra3 Bc5 31.Rxd3 { here he offered a draw } 31...Qxa4 32.Qe2 ( 32.f5 Qa1 33.Qg2 gxf5 $36 ) 32...Qd7 33.Qe4 $3 { centralisation !! the ONLY solution in such positions! } 33...a4 34.b4 $1 axb3 35.Rxb3 b6 ( 35...b5 36.f5 gxf5 ( 36...Qxf5 37.Qxf5 gxf5 38.Rxb5 Kg7 ) 37.Qf4 $36 ) 36.Rf3 Qa7 37.Qd3 ( 37.f5 $4 { that was my last trap !! } 37...Qa2+ 38.Kh3 ( 38.Kh1 Qa1+ 39.Kg2 Qg1+ 40.Kh3 Qh1# ) 38...Bg1 $1 39.Qe8+ Kg7 40.f6+ Kh7 41.Rf2 Bxf2 42.Qf8 Qe6+ $1 43.Kg2 Qxf6 $19 { allthough as he said..he failed to see 41.Rf2 } ) 37...Qa2+ 

