 { This lecture finishes the examination of White's rare lines. After } 1.e4 c5 2.Nf3 d6 3.d4 cxd4 4.Nxd4 Nf6 5.Nc3 a6 { the most important deviation is } 6.Nb3 $5 { This is one of the best rare moves. We will soon reach an unclear and complicated position with chances for both sides! It would be pointless once again to try to memorize every possible move and idea! } ( { The lecture also examines } 6.Bd3 { This is another fashionable line without deep ideas. The idea is to just develop the pieces and play chess! Quite often White's knight from d4 will go to e2 and then to g3 for kingside attacks. We hope that this Ng3 will turn out to be misplaced. } ) ( 6.Qf3 $6 { One of the most unfortunate 6th moves by white in the Najdorf! The queen is very misplaced there and Black has a very good chance to quickly size the initiative! He just needs to know a few good moves! } ) 

