 { [%evp 0,44,41,28,51,56,81,70,67,36,34,21,70,24,107,50,38,39,39,33,49,0,-8,-24, -7,-38,41,26,54,47,47,26,26,26,92,92,102,72,47,12,12,-180,48,-45,14,-251,-264] } 1.e4 c5 2.Nf3 d6 3.d4 cxd4 4.Nxd4 Nf6 5.Nc3 a6 6.Qf3 g6 { clearly the best move. } 7.h3 Bg7 8.Be3 O-O 9.O-O-O Nc6 { the correct move. } 10.g4 ( 10.Nxc6 bxc6 11.e5 Nd5 { with really good play. } 12.Nxd5 cxd5 13.Qxd5 Be6 ) 10...Bd7 11.Qg2 { Intending to play g5 and follow up Nh5 with Be2. } ( 11.g5 Nh5 { important move to stop White's attack. } ) 11...Rc8 { It is better to attack with pieces here. } 12.f4 Na5 13.Kb1 ( 13.g5 Nh5 { intending e5/Nxf4-e5 next. } 14.Be2 Nc4 ) 13...Nc4 { is also good enough. } ( 13...Rxc3 { Whenever we have a chance, we should always sacrifice on c3! } 14.bxc3 ) ( 13...b5 { is quite slow. It is better to attack with pieces in this position. } 14.Bd3 b4 15.Nd5 Nxd5 16.exd5 ) 14.Bxc4 Rxc4 15.e5 Ne8 16.Qxb7 Nc7 17.exd6 exd6 18.Qb3 d5 19.Nde2 Qa8 20.Qa3 Rb8 21.Qd6 Rxc3 22.Bd4 Qc6 

