 { [%evp 0,52,16,28,46,51,106,88,72,64,55,49,88,26,59,37,56,17,33,29,66,43,64,22, 17,-10,52,42,39,-56,2,-7,-13,-104,-46,-46,-36,-36,-48,-85,-67,-55,38,3,9,-24, 87,-12,163,167,247,-846,-894,-29995,-29996] } 1.e4 c5 2.Nf3 d6 3.d4 cxd4 4.Nxd4 Nf6 5.Nc3 a6 6.Qd3 { a very very rare move still leading to unclear play. Just check the plans and the ideas! } 6...g6 ( 6...e6 { looks passive. } 7.Be2 Be7 8.O-O Nc6 9.Nxc6 bxc6 10.b3 O-O 11.Bb2 { Intending Qg3 } ) 7.Bg5 Bg7 8.O-O-O Nbd7 9.Be2 Qc7 ( 9...b5 { appears premature. } 10.Nd5 ) ( 9...Nc5 { makes the knight clumsy. } 10.Qe3 Qc7 11.Bxf6 Bxf6 12.Nd5 ) ( 9...Ne5 10.Qg3 Bd7 11.f4 Nc6 12.e5 ) 10.h4 ( 10.Nd5 Nxd5 11.exd5 Nf6 { Planning Qa5 targeting a2,d5 pawns. } ) 10...h5 { stopping white's kingside attack. } ( 10...O-O { is sucide } 11.h5 Ne5 12.Qg3 ) ( 10...h6 { ideally this would be our choice but after } 11.Bxf6 $1 ( 11.Bd2 Nc5 ( 11...e5 12.Ndb5 ) ( 11...h5 ) ) 11...Nxf6 12.h5 { White has very active play. } ( 12.g4 ) ) 11.f4 ( 11.Kb1 e5 { is a mistake, if White has not play f4. } ( 11...O-O 12.f4 e5 13.fxe5 ( 13.Nb3 exf4 14.Bxf4 Ne5 ) 13...dxe5 ) 12.Nb3 ) 11...O-O { Planning b5-Bb7 } 12.Qe3 ( 12.Kb1 b5 13.a3 Rb8 { another very typical idea. Intending b4 } ( 13...Bb7 14.Qe3 e5 15.fxe5 dxe5 ( 15...Nxe5 ) 16.Nb3 Rac8 ) ) 12...e5 { is also a very serious move. } 13.Nb3 ( 13.fxe5 dxe5 14.Nb3 b5 15.Rhf1 Bb7 $1 ( 15...b4 16.Nd5 Nxd5 17.exd5 ) ( 15...Rb8 { Intending Rb6. } ) 16.a3 Rae8 { Intending Re6. } ( 16...Rac8 17.Bd3 ( 17.Qf3 Bxe4 ) ( 17.Qd3 Qb6 18.Kb1 Qe6 { stabilizing the position. } ) 17...Ba8 18.Qf3 Qb6 $1 19.Bd2 ( 19.Kb1 Rxc3 20.bxc3 Qe6 ) 19...Qe6 $17 ) 17.Kb1 Re6 ) 13...b5 $1 { Intending b4 to chase both the knights. } 14.f5 $6 ( 14.fxe5 Nxe5 ( 14...dxe5 { is possibly better. } ) 15.Bxf6 { sometimes Black can also allow this. } 15...Bxf6 16.Nd5 Qd8 17.Nxf6+ Qxf6 18.Kb1 Bg4 $1 $17 ( 18...Bb7 ) ) 14...Bb7 ( 14...b4 $1 { is better. } ) 15.fxg6 ( 15.g4 { would be a better but it is unclear. } 15...b4 ) 15...fxg6 16.Bf3 ( 16.a3 Rac8 17.Bd3 Nc5 ) 16...b4 $1 { Black is clearly better. } ( 16...Rac8 17.a3 { it is not so easy to attack anymore. } ) 17.Nd5 Bxd5 $1 18.exd5 a5 $1 ( 18...e4 19.Be2 ) 19.Kb1 a4 $1 20.Nd2 e4 $1 { you need to play active chess in the Najdorf. } 21.Nxe4 ( 21.Bxe4 Ng4 22.Qg3 Nde5 ) 21...Nxe4 22.Qxe4 ( 22.Bxe4 Rfe8 { White has many problems which can't be solved. } ) 22...b3 23.Qxg6 ( 23.cxb3 axb3 24.a3 Rxa3 25.bxa3 Qc3 26.Qe6+ Kh8 ) 23...bxa2+ 24.Kxa2 ( 24.Ka1 a3 ) 24...a3 25.b3 Qc3 26.Rb1 Qb2+ 

