 { [%evp 0,108,16,28,97,43,86,86,86,56,53,53,82,16,32,14,8,-1,20,6,47,17,16,-1,1, 11,-1,-26,32,26,50,43,15,10,3,3,3,-6,11,9,6,-31,-8,-16,-36,-22,-10,-60,-48,-15, -17,-23,-43,-66,-6,-38,-58,-66,-76,-82,-89,-86,-72,-63,-78,-87,-81,-102,-92, -95,-87,-72,-93,-70,-70,-77,-62,-80,-87,-72,-73,-67,-78,-96,-91,-108,-105,-110, -103,-129,-98,-98,-101,-136,-169,-144,-266,-266,-295,-294,-294,-337,-345,-337, -293,-316,-233,-289,-331,-494,-507] } 1.e4 c5 2.Nf3 d6 3.d4 cxd4 4.Nxd4 Nf6 5.Nc3 a6 6.Bd3 { This move is trendy now a days. The idea is to get out of the book. } 6...e5 ( 6...Nbd7 { intending g6-Bg7 setup. } 7.O-O ( 7.Be3 g6 ( 7...e5 8.Nb3 ( 8.Nf5 g6 { When we play g6, our plan is not always Bg7. Often, we just want to remove White's knight from f5. } ( 8...b5 9.Bg5 { White will win for sure. } ) 9.Nh6 ( 9.Ng3 h5 10.h3 b5 { Intending Bb7 next. } ) 9...Nc5 ) 8...b5 ) ) 7...e5 { is a terrible move as after } 8.Nf5 { White is better. } ) 7.Nde2 ( 7.Nb3 Be7 8.O-O O-O 9.Be3 ( 9.f4 b5 ) 9...Be6 10.f4 ( 10.Qe2 Nbd7 11.f4 exf4 { we are fine. } ) 10...exf4 ) 7...Be7 8.O-O O-O 9.Ng3 Re8 { ...g6 is also playable. } 10.Bc4 ( 10.Nd5 Nxd5 11.exd5 g6 12.f4 { with unclear position. } ) 10...Be6 11.Nd5 Nbd7 12.Be3 Rc8 13.Bb3 Bf8 ( 13...Bxd5 { is also possible. } 14.Bxd5 { the best move. } ( 14.exd5 g6 { Intending Bf8-Bg7 } ) 14...Nxd5 15.exd5 Bg5 ( 15...g6 16.f4 ) ) 14.c3 Qa5 15.Nxf6+ Nxf6 16.Bg5 Nd7 17.Qe2 Nc5 18.Bxe6 Nxe6 19.Be3 d5 20.exd5 Qxd5 21.Rfd1 Qc6 22.Qg4 g6 23.f3 Bc5 24.Bxc5 Qxc5+ 25.Kh1 Rcd8 26.Qe4 b5 27.Qc2 f5 28.Qb3 Kf7 29.a4 Qc4 30.Qxc4 bxc4 31.Nf1 Rd3 32.Re1 Nc5 33.Kg1 f4 34.Re2 e4 35.fxe4 Rxe4 36.Rxe4 Nxe4 37.Re1 Nc5 38.a5 Rd5 39.h4 Kf6 40.Nh2 Kf5 41.Nf3 Nd3 42.Re7 Rxa5 43.Rxh7 Nxb2 44.Rf7+ Ke4 45.Kh2 Nd1 46.Rd7 Ne3 47.Rd6 Ng4+ 48.Kh3 Nf2+ 49.Kh2 Ra1 50.Ng1 Ng4+ 51.Kh1 Ne5 52.Kh2 Ra2 53.Kh1 a5 54.Nf3 Ra1+ 

